CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 16, 1957, pg. A9, reads: "Victorious Alphas - In a recent gridiron battle the undergraduate chapters of Alpha Phi Alpha and Omega Psi Phi Fraternities met to decide the winner of the "Whiskey Bowl" trophy. The Alphas proved themselves to be the champs by winning, 6-0, and proudly display their cup.  The winners are, seated from left to right: T. Burnett, H. Dorman, R. Nickols, R. Goggin and C. Mack.  Standing: A. Hughley, D.L. Washington, M. Lee, C. Jackson, W. McCallum. R. LeGrande, J. Douglass, C. Witcher, D. Washington, S. Booker and G. Freeman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of sixteen undergraduate Alpha Phi Alpha winners of the Whiskey Bowl, seated from left: T. Burnett, H. Dorman, R. Nickols, R. Goggin, C. Mack; standing: A. Hughley, D. L. Washington, M. Lee, C. Jackson, W. McCallum, R. LeGrande, J. Douglass, C. Witcher, D. Washington, S. Booker, and G. Freeman, gathered around trophy, another version
